    "name": "YT Backend API Documentation",
    "description": "# YT Backend API Documentation\n\nA production-ready REST API for a personal finance tracker — **YT Backend**. This API enables users to register, authenticate, manage financial records (income/expenses), and view dashboard analytics.\n\n---\n\n## Base URL\n\n```\n{{base_url}}\n```\n\nSet `base_url` to `http://localhost:3000` for local development.\n\n---\n\n## Authentication\n\nThis API uses **JWT-based cookie authentication**. After a successful login, the server sets an `HttpOnly` cookie named `token`. All protected routes require this cookie to be present.\n\n**Login flow:**\n1. `POST /api/auth/register` — Create a new account\n2. `POST /api/auth/login` — Receive JWT cookie\n3. Include `Cookie: token={{jwt_token}}` header on all subsequent requests\n\nSet the `jwt_token` global variable to your JWT after login.\n\n---\n\n## Roles & Access Control\n\n| Role | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `user` | Default role. Can manage their own records and view their dashboard. |\n| `admin` | Full access. Can view all users, update roles and statuses. |\n| `analyst` | Read-only access to analytics and records. |\n| `viewer` | Basic read-only access. |\n\n---\n\n## Global Variables\n\n| Variable | Description | Example |\n|----------|-------------|---------|\n| `base_url` | Base URL of the API server | `http://localhost:3000` |\n| `jwt_token` | JWT token received after login | *(set after login)* |\n\n---\n\n## Folders\n\n| Folder | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| **Auth** | Registration, login, logout, and current user endpoints |\n| **Users** | Admin-only user management endpoints |\n| **Records** | CRUD operations for financial records (income/expenses) |\n| **Dashboard** | Analytics: summary, categories, trends, and recent activity |\n\n---\n\n## Common Response Codes\n\n| Code | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `200` | OK — Request succeeded |\n| `201` | Created — Resource successfully created |\n| `400` | Bad Request — Validation error or missing fields |\n| `401` | Unauthorized — Missing or invalid JWT token |\n| `403` | Forbidden — Insufficient permissions for this role |\n| `500` | Internal Server Error — Unexpected server failure |\n\n---\n\n## Endpoint Reference\n\n### Auth\n| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| `POST` | `/api/auth/register` | Register a new user |\n| `POST` | `/api/auth/login` | Login and receive JWT cookie |\n| `GET` | `/api/auth/me` | Get currently authenticated user |\n| `POST` | `/api/auth/logout` | Logout and clear JWT cookie |\n\n### Users *(Admin only)*\n| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| `GET` | `/api/users/users` | Get all users |\n| `GET` | `/api/users/user/:userId` | Get user by ID |\n| `PATCH` | `/api/users/user/:userId/role` | Update user role |\n| `PATCH` | `/api/users/user/:userId/status` | Update user active status |\n\n### Records\n| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| `GET` | `/api/records` | Get all records for authenticated user |\n| `POST` | `/api/records` | Create a new financial record |\n| `GET` | `/api/records/:recordId` | Get a specific record by ID |\n| `PUT` | `/api/records/:recordId` | Update a specific record |\n\n### Dashboard\n| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| `GET` | `/api/dashboard/summary` | Get financial summary (income, expense, balance) |\n| `GET` | `/api/dashboard/categories` | Get spending breakdown by category |\n| `GET` | `/api/dashboard/trends/monthly` | Get monthly income/expense trends |\n| `GET` | `/api/dashboard/trends/weekly` | Get weekly income/expense trends |\n| `GET` | `/api/dashboard/recent` | Get most recent financial records |",
