            "description": "## Login\n\nAuthenticates a user with email and password. On success, a signed JWT is issued and stored in an HTTP-only cookie named `token`.\n\n**Access:** Public (no authentication required)\n\n### Request Body\n| Field | Type | Required | Description |\n|-------|------|----------|-------------|\n| email | string | Yes | Registered email address |\n| password | string | Yes | Account password |\n\n### Notes\n- JWT is stored as an HTTP-only cookie (`token`) — not returned in the response body\n- Cookie expiry: 7 days\n- Use this token for all subsequent authenticated requests\n\n### Response Examples\n\n**200 OK**\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"message\": \"Login successful\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"_id\": \"69cd709ef6d0d02290c9de6e\",\n    \"name\": \"Suraj Sharma\",\n    \"email\": \"suraj.sharma@example.com\",\n    \"role\": \"admin\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**400 Bad Request** – Missing fields\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"message\": \"Email and password are required\"\n}\n```\n\n**401 Unauthorized** – Invalid credentials\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"message\": \"Invalid email or password\"\n}\n```\n\n**500 Internal Server Error**\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": false,\n  \"message\": \"Internal server error. Please try again later.\"\n}\n```"
